    <title>Working With Mail Pieces</title>
    <para>The following sections describe working with mail pieces. You can display a list of the mail pieces. The following actions are supported in the <guilabel>Mail Pieces</guilabel> view:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="display_mailPieces"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="filter_mailPieces"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="reprint_mailPieces"/></para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_mailPieces"><?dbhtml filename="SearchMediaView.html" ?><title>Listing Mail Pieces</title>
        <para>You can display an overview of the configured mail pieces in the workspace of the <guilabel>Mail Pieces</guilabel> view.</para>
        <mediaobject><alt>Screenshot Mail Pieces view</alt><imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_mailPieceView.png" width="14cm"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>The overview table displays the following information for each mail piece by default:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>ID</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The unique identifier of the mail piece (sequential number).</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Envelope</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The envelope configuration associated with the mail piece.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Product class</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Specification of the (user-defined) product class to which the mail piece is assigned.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Sequence</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Sequence ID</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Weight</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Mail piece weight.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Sheets</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Number of sheets in the mail piece.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="filter_mailPieces">
        <title>Filtering Mail Pieces</title>
        <para>Use this action to filter the overview of existing mail pieces.</para>
        <para>Proceed as follows to filter the existing documents and thus reduce the number of displayed documents.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Switch to the <guilabel>Mail Pieces</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the view, place the cursor in the text field <guilabel>Filter</guilabel>.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>You can filter the existing mail pieces by ID (simple filter) or by other parameters (for more information about filter criteria, see <xref linkend="db_pil_wui_filterSettings"/>).</para>
            </step>
        </procedure>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="reprint_mailPieces">
        <title>Reprinting Mail Pieces</title>
        <para>Use this action to manually trigger reprinting for one or more mail pieces.</para>
        <para>Proceed as follows to reprint selected mail pieces.</para>
        <procedure>
            <step>
                <para>Switch to the <guilabel>Mail Pieces</guilabel> view.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>Select at least one mail piece from the overview table.</para>
                <para>Tick the checkbox next to the desired entry to select it.</para>
            </step>
            <step>
                <para>In the navigation bar of the view, click <inlinemediaobject><alt>Button Reprint</alt><imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/btn_reprint.png" scalefit="1"/>
                        </imageobject></inlinemediaobject> to initiate reprinting for the selected mail piece.</para>
            </step>
            <result><para>Reprinting is started.</para></result>
        </procedure>
    </sect1><!-- Scanner-Eingabe konfigurieren --><xi:include href="../../../../../../scannersettings/com.compart.documentation.scanner.settings/resources/en-US/scanner-settings.xml"/> 
